Top Ten Provinces by Population Under 5

The census shows a young population, as anticipated. Some 19 percent of Afghans in Pakistan are
under the age of five, compared to about 14.8 percent of Pakistanâ€™s population in this age group.
This demographic profile, underlines the fact that much of the Afghan population was born in exile,
points to the considerable challenge ahead for any Afghan government to provide schools and
employment for returnees.
